// Break
// The break is a control transfer statement.
// It is a keyword.
// It is used in the body of loop to terminate the execution of the loop.
// When the break statement is encountered inside a loop, the loop iteration stops and
//      control moves to the first statement after the loop.
// Break CAN ALSO BE USED IN THE BODY OF SWITCH........

// example----- SOME PROBLEM
// for(int i=1;i<=10;i++){
//     for(int j=1;j<=5;j++){
//         if(i+j >8)
//             break
//         print(I+J);
//     }
// }        In this example, the break only exits One loop, BAD BAD BAD BAD

